    "narrative": [
      "Shift Handoff — Cluster Observability (as of 2026-03-24 23:59:59Z)\n\nURGENT (act now)\n1) Degraded GPU host: chi-gpu-001 (training-a, rack r12)\n   - CPU load 0.92 + memory pressure 0.88 (highest in inventory sample); status=degraded.\n   - Next checks: top CPU/mem consumers, kernel/OOM events, swap/thrashing, GPU job placement/noisy neighbor, node health (ECC/Xid if available), consider drain if instability is confirmed.\n\n2) Queue backlog concentrated in two partitions (scheduler pressure)\n   - Pending jobs: mi3001x=36, mi2104x=26 (together ~89% of observed pending).\n   - Next checks: down/drained nodes in those partitions, reservation/QOS limits, fairshare, recent node failures, and whether capacity can be temporarily shifted or job limits adjusted.\n\n3) Storage pressure warning: dal-storage-017 (analytics-b, rack r44)\n   - Memory pressure 0.79 + disk pressure 0.73 (highest disk pressure in inventory sample); status=warning.\n   - Next checks: disk fullness vs IOPS/latency, filesystem errors, RAID/SMART, top talkers, cache eviction pressure; consider proactive cleanup/migration if nearing thresholds.\n\nMEDIUM-TERM WATCH (monitor during shift)\n1) Hot GPUs / thermal headroom\n   - Top temps: 82°C (k002-004-v5:8000 card0), 81°C (k002-004-v7:8000 card0), 79°C (k002-004-v1:8000 card0).\n   - Watch for sustained >80°C and any correlating throttling/perf complaints; check fans/airflow and recent workload changes.\n\n2) High CPU saturation on several partitions, but low pending\n   - CPU sat=1.0 on mi3008x/mi3258x/mi3508x while pending is only 1–2 each (busy but currently flowing).\n   - Watch for backlog growth; if pending rises, reassess drained capacity and scheduling constraints.\n\nCONFIDENCE / CAVEATS\n- Inventory snapshot covers only 4 hosts (not fleet-representative); treat host-level rankings as “sampled signals” until you confirm via broader fleet views.\n- VictoriaMetrics shows 72 instrumented hosts and provides point-in-time vectors for pending/saturation/temps in this preview; re-run/refresh if you suspect recent state changes or missing series.\n- Partition CPU saturation and pending jobs indicate user impact risk but do not alone prove capacity shortage (policy/QOS/reservations can be the primary constraint)."
